Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

CO: RMW, REP: Drost, CLERK: Liddle. ADA:  Alexis S. Mckinley   DF ATTY:  Jessie Gwynn Weber   DF:  Olad Shariff Omar appeared. Case called at 2:24 p.m. Court notes this matter is set for a plea and sentencing hearing. Atty Weber recites agreement. Requesting for expungement. State has complied with Victims Rights. Court reads charge and maximum penalty. DE pleads NO CONTEST to Ct 1 in 16CM106. DE sworn. Crt reviews plea questionnaire and informs DE of rights. Crt finds DE freely, voluntarily and knowingly waives rights and makes plea. Attorney's stipulate to the facts. Crt accepts plea, finds factual basis and finds DE guilty of Ct 1 Theft Movable Property in 16CM106. On motion of the State without objecton, Crt dismisses 16CF50 without prejudice. Sentencing arguments. DE makes statement. 20 days to file appeal. 

Crt orders in 16CM106:

- S/W 1 year probation. Report to probation no later than 4:00 p.m. today. Bond will remain in effect until reports to probation

- $300.00 fine inclusive of costs

- Complete all other programming as deemed appropriate by the COMPAS assessment and the Department of Corrections

- Restitution in the amount of $1,167.00 payable to the Sprint Store

- It is hereby ordered, as a condition of the defendant's bond/bail in the above-captioned case, that he/she have absolutely NO CONTACT whatsoever with the complaining witness, or with any of the following named persons and/or locations, Sprint, AT&T Stores & co defendant's.  The term "no contact" is hereby defined as no contact in person, by telephone, by way of electronic device, email, facsimile, social media including but not limited to texting, Facebook, Twitter, contact through the mail, and/or through a third person.  The aforementioned condition of bond/bail is set pursuant to Sec. 969.02(3)(d), Wis Stats.
